text.tspan: Explanation
Levels in this game are related to themaximum satisfiability problemin computational theory.
It has many real-world applications, including route planning, circuit layout, genomics, and
software verification.
When you play, you are helping to find the best solutions to maximum satisfiability problems by
assigning values in a logical formula!

Editors
To play, click and drag to use editors to change the color of variables.
Your goal is to match the colors of as many constraints as possible to remove paradoxes
and beat the target score!
Make power plants emit light energy.
Make power plants emit dark energy.
Try all possible combinations to find the best type of energy
for each power plant to emit; may be slow.
Try random combinations to find good types of energy for each
power plant to emit; fast, but may miss the best combinations.
Engineers
To play, click and drag to deploy engineers and change the energy type emitted from power plants.
Your goal is to match the energy types of as many factories as possible to remove blackouts
and beat the target score!
